						               													<description>In Sherlock Holmes, detectives venture to the darkest parts of London trying to solve one of six different Sherlock Holmes cases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game, each player is given one of the six cases to solve (kept secret). On their turn, players move their detective piece one or two spaces on the board. Travelling from location to location, they collect clues to be the first to solve their case. Once all their clues have been collected, the player must arrest the criminal before the case is finally solved. Once a player has solved a case, every other player has ten turns to solve their case (losing 1 point each turn). The game ends once all players have solved their case (or if the last players have reached -10 points). All players who have solved their case count up their points (from their case tiles and if they successfully found the criminal) and the player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
